eholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":40},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":393659,"mol_weight":0,"name":"BSA Molecular Biology Grade ","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/products\/b9000-bsa-molecular-biology-grade#Product%20Information","sku":"B9000S","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"New England Biolabs","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"https:\/\/www.neb.com\/","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/2.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":2},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}},{"id":393660,"mol_weight":0,"name":"Recombinant Ribonuclease Inhibitor","linfor":"","url":"https:\/\/www.takarabio.com\/products\/cdna-synthesis\/cdna-synthesis-accessories\/rnase-inhibitors\/recombinant-ribonuclease-inhibitor","sku":"2313A","cas_number":"","rrid":"","public":0,"vendor":{"name":"Takara","affiliation":null,"affiliations":[],"username":null,"link":"http:\/\/www.takara-bio.co.jp\/research.htm","image":{"source":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png","placeholder":"https:\/\/www.protocols.io\/img\/vendors\/placeholder.png"},"badges":[],"research_interests":null,"blocked_by_you":false,"blocked_you":false,"hide_following":false,"id":184},"can_edit":0,"stats":{"total_protocols":0}}],"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>This protocol details a step in the workflow for our contribution to the BRAIN Initiative Cell Census Network           (BICCN) \u2013 Comprehensive Center on Mouse Brain Cell Atlas (U19) project. In previous steps of the workflow, we collected flash-frozen tissue from select areas of the murine cortex. Here, we dounce homogenize and digest the tissue in order to isolate the nuclei into a PBS, BSA, and RNase inhibitor solution, which is then FACS sorted to isolate nuclei subpopulations of choice. The protocol is adapted from Habib et al., <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Massively parallel single nucleus RNA-seq with dronc-seq,<\/span><span> Nature Methods, 2017, with additional commentary by Eugene Drokhlynasky and Ehsan Habibi of the Regev lab. Per Gene, this method for nuclei extraction works best; Per Ehsan, this method works very well with mouse brain tissue.<\/span><\/div><\/div>","changed_on":1586872697}